1
00:00:22,464 --> 00:00:26,432
♪Should we forget yesterday's sorrows♪

2
00:00:26,432 --> 00:00:29,728
♪And the dazed confusion♪

3
00:00:30,976 --> 00:00:33,681
♪Should we let go of♪

4
00:00:33,681 --> 00:00:35,904
♪The stubborn madness♪

5
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:39,072
♪And naive recklessness now♪

6
00:00:40,192 --> 00:00:43,840
♪Those years, those faces♪

7
00:00:44,992 --> 00:00:48,763
♪Those old scars we can't erase♪

8
00:00:49,824 --> 00:00:52,460
♪Tears streaming, facing the light♪

9
00:00:53,152 --> 00:00:57,594
♪Piercing the sorrow within♪

10
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:12,736
♪The road ahead's long,
stumbling all the way♪

11
00:01:13,536 --> 00:01:18,076
♪The wounds we've borne
are medals hidden within♪

12
00:01:18,336 --> 00:01:22,391
♪Standing alone on an open plain♪

13
00:01:23,168 --> 00:01:26,851
♪We gaze at the stars♪

14
00:01:31,228 --> 00:01:34,816
=The Dream Maker=

15
00:01:35,087 --> 00:01:37,912
=Episode 37=

16
00:01:38,284 --> 00:01:39,924
Xia! Xia!

17
00:01:40,165 --> 00:01:40,764
Guan.

18
00:01:41,645 --> 00:01:42,605
- Mr. Xia
- Mr. Xia.

19
00:01:42,965 --> 00:01:44,284
I'll go. I'll talk to him.

20
00:01:48,085 --> 00:01:49,965
We shouldn't have brought Mr. Xia here.

21
00:01:50,645 --> 00:01:53,365
All for nothing.

22
00:01:54,324 --> 00:01:56,404
Let's just forget it.

23
00:01:57,564 --> 00:01:59,124
What should we do about the land?

24
00:02:01,204 --> 00:02:03,924
Mr. Zheng, I have a bold idea.

25
00:02:12,245 --> 00:02:13,684
Hotpot,

26
00:02:14,485 --> 00:02:17,005
massage services,

27
00:02:17,496 --> 00:02:18,805
and ads in between movies.

28
00:02:22,765 --> 00:02:24,245
That was your idea, right?

29
00:02:27,164 --> 00:02:28,884
Chunlai, do you mean

30
00:02:29,325 --> 00:02:30,485
my idea was great?

31
00:02:31,965 --> 00:02:33,205
Thanks to you,

32
00:02:34,724 --> 00:02:35,884
I can't take it back.

33
00:02:37,004 --> 00:02:37,965
But I can point this.

34
00:02:38,844 --> 00:02:40,325
If we don't clear this up today,

35
00:02:41,045 --> 00:02:43,256
you better think twice
before I lift this finger.

36
00:02:43,448 --> 00:02:44,085
Understood?

37
00:02:48,004 --> 00:02:49,560
Why aren't Mr. Zheng and Ms. Li here?

38
00:02:49,944 --> 00:02:51,045
Just the two of you?

39
00:02:51,684 --> 00:02:52,485
Looking down on us?

40
00:02:52,485 --> 00:02:53,684
No, that's not it.

41
00:02:53,884 --> 00:02:54,485
No, wait.

42
00:02:54,485 --> 00:02:55,365
What do you mean?

43
00:02:55,365 --> 00:02:56,245
Wait.

44
00:02:56,485 --> 00:02:57,564
I didn't mean that.

45
00:02:57,604 --> 00:03:00,485
Well, the whole country
is promoting innovation.

46
00:03:00,805 --> 00:03:02,325
Isn't my idea one of a kind?

47
00:03:02,325 --> 00:03:03,045
- Yes.
- Yes.

48
00:03:03,045 --> 00:03:03,805
One of a kind.

49
00:03:03,805 --> 00:03:04,604
Right?

50
00:03:05,245 --> 00:03:06,164
Good job.

51
00:03:06,805 --> 00:03:07,965
Exactly, one of a kind.

52
00:03:08,444 --> 00:03:09,004
One of a kind.

53
00:03:09,004 --> 00:03:09,485
Yes.

54
00:03:09,564 --> 00:03:10,164
We admit that.

55
00:03:11,045 --> 00:03:12,604
Alright, Xie, let me say something.

56
00:03:15,164 --> 00:03:17,045
There are quite a few people here.

57
00:03:17,284 --> 00:03:18,925
All talking at once

58
00:03:18,925 --> 00:03:20,284
will spoil the broth.

59
00:03:20,404 --> 00:03:21,284
I suggest

60
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:23,654
the one with the most shares

61
00:03:23,832 --> 00:03:25,365
who can make a decision stays.

62
00:03:25,485 --> 00:03:26,884
The rest, step out for a bit.

63
00:03:26,884 --> 00:03:27,444
Well,

64
00:03:27,765 --> 00:03:29,925
the ten people here
are all shareholders.

65
00:03:29,925 --> 00:03:30,884
Each one has

66
00:03:30,965 --> 00:03:32,205
10 percent of shares.

67
00:03:32,404 --> 00:03:34,205
If there's a problem,
we're all responsible.

68
00:03:34,205 --> 00:03:34,925
- Right.
- Right.

69
00:03:35,045 --> 00:03:36,844
Perfect ten people, just right.

70
00:03:36,844 --> 00:03:37,844
- Right.
- Exactly.

71
00:03:42,684 --> 00:03:44,844
During night school, in this very room,

72
00:03:44,925 --> 00:03:47,485
I mentioned
the share responsibility system,

73
00:03:48,884 --> 00:03:49,925
right?

74
00:03:50,245 --> 00:03:51,004
Yes.

75
00:03:51,325 --> 00:03:53,325
And you fell asleep that night

76
00:03:53,325 --> 00:03:54,645
when I asked you the question.

77
00:03:54,645 --> 00:03:55,925
That night, only two of us.

78
00:03:55,965 --> 00:03:56,965
But it's ten people now.

79
00:03:57,004 --> 00:03:58,444
So shares can split equally.

80
00:03:58,485 --> 00:04:00,844
The system requires share distribution.

81
00:04:01,085 --> 00:04:03,245
Someone has to be
the controlling stakeholder!

82
00:04:03,365 --> 00:04:04,604
We all share responsibility!

83
00:04:04,645 --> 00:04:05,645
Yes! All responsible.

84
00:04:05,844 --> 00:04:06,564
Shut up!

85
00:04:06,925 --> 00:04:07,765
Shut up.

86
00:04:07,965 --> 00:04:08,564
Shut up!

87
00:04:08,925 --> 00:04:10,724
I'm trying to help you!

88
00:04:11,444 --> 00:04:12,004
Enough.

89
00:04:17,164 --> 00:04:18,404
- Are you okay?
- It's okay.

90
00:04:18,484 --> 00:04:19,364
- I won't speak.
- Okay.

91
00:04:19,364 --> 00:04:19,724
Go ahead.

92
00:04:19,724 --> 00:04:20,325
Right.

93
00:04:20,565 --> 00:04:22,484
Calm down.

94
00:04:23,685 --> 00:04:25,604
It's just a theater issue, right?

95
00:04:27,205 --> 00:04:29,085
On behalf of all shareholders,

96
00:04:29,645 --> 00:04:32,244
we promise to fix everything
within a month, okay?

97
00:04:32,445 --> 00:04:33,005
Just a month.

98
00:04:33,765 --> 00:04:36,205
That's well said.

99
00:04:36,645 --> 00:04:38,724
I agree to make a rectification.

100
00:04:39,005 --> 00:04:39,965
No problem.

101
00:04:40,284 --> 00:04:43,005
I'll remove the hotpot
and massage services.

102
00:04:43,164 --> 00:04:45,044
But the ads

103
00:04:45,804 --> 00:04:46,525
can't be removed.

104
00:04:46,645 --> 00:04:49,765
- The theater relies on ad revenue.
- Right.

105
00:04:49,765 --> 00:04:51,445
- We have to make money, right?
- Right. Make money.

106
00:04:51,445 --> 00:04:52,244
Keep massages.

107
00:04:52,924 --> 00:04:53,724
Really?

108
00:04:53,965 --> 00:04:54,525
Keep massages.

109
00:04:54,685 --> 00:04:55,205
See?

110
00:04:55,284 --> 00:04:56,685
Xie, I disagree.

111
00:04:56,924 --> 00:04:58,924
Everything should be canceled.

112
00:04:58,924 --> 00:04:59,844
Don't overthink.

113
00:05:00,364 --> 00:05:01,885
Hotpot smells.

114
00:05:01,965 --> 00:05:02,244
Right.

115
00:05:02,364 --> 00:05:03,364
It'll disturb others.

116
00:05:03,844 --> 00:05:06,044
Massage is comfortable.

117
00:05:06,284 --> 00:05:06,604
Yes.

118
00:05:06,804 --> 00:05:09,804
Right? You can watch the movie this way

119
00:05:09,924 --> 00:05:11,244
or this way.

120
00:05:11,604 --> 00:05:12,685
Also,

121
00:05:13,044 --> 00:05:14,325
you can be like this.

122
00:05:14,484 --> 00:05:15,924
- Xie.
- Just relaxed.

123
00:05:16,005 --> 00:05:18,244
Xie, just speak. Stop fidgeting.

124
00:05:18,284 --> 00:05:19,525
My opinion is

125
00:05:19,885 --> 00:05:21,645
that hotpots,

126
00:05:21,724 --> 00:05:23,044
massage services and ads

127
00:05:23,044 --> 00:05:25,844
will disturb other viewers.

128
00:05:26,005 --> 00:05:27,765
Just avoid that!

129
00:05:27,844 --> 00:05:29,965
If massage's hard and people yell,
it'll be disruptive.

130
00:05:29,965 --> 00:05:31,284
But you can time it perfectly.

131
00:05:31,325 --> 00:05:31,565
Right.

132
00:05:31,604 --> 00:05:33,525
If someone screams
during a stabbing scene,

133
00:05:33,645 --> 00:05:35,765
and viewers yell at the same time,

134
00:05:35,965 --> 00:05:37,404
that'd create surround sound.

135
00:05:37,404 --> 00:05:37,844
Great!

136
00:05:39,244 --> 00:05:40,205
Just find solutions.

137
00:05:40,604 --> 00:05:43,085
Every movie has its own key moments.

138
00:05:43,244 --> 00:05:45,565
Global movies are already in 4D now.

139
00:05:46,164 --> 00:05:47,685
You all know it, right?

140
00:05:48,125 --> 00:05:48,765
Tan.

141
00:05:48,965 --> 00:05:50,885
It has sound

142
00:05:50,924 --> 00:05:51,844
and physical effects.

143
00:05:51,885 --> 00:05:52,645
I'm just...

144
00:05:52,804 --> 00:05:54,005
My vote is to ban them all.

145
00:05:54,005 --> 00:05:55,445
No, we should encourage innovations.

146
00:05:55,525 --> 00:05:56,085
Tan.

147
00:05:56,404 --> 00:05:58,765
One theater becomes two, then, three.

148
00:05:58,804 --> 00:06:00,924
We can build a chain and expand it!

149
00:06:01,085 --> 00:06:02,445
Everyone wants that!

150
00:06:03,445 --> 00:06:05,484
Do you know how many bosses have left?

151
00:06:06,325 --> 00:06:07,645
Yuehai has no land left.

152
00:06:08,005 --> 00:06:10,085
How to expand? Please tell us.

153
00:06:11,924 --> 00:06:13,752
The bosses who left

154
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:14,804
said that

155
00:06:15,325 --> 00:06:16,844
Yuehai has no land.

156
00:06:17,164 --> 00:06:19,645
Things will only deteriorate from here.

157
00:06:20,445 --> 00:06:21,164
You know that?

158
00:06:21,244 --> 00:06:22,205
How could I not know?

159
00:06:22,205 --> 00:06:23,844
You all know

160
00:06:24,085 --> 00:06:26,924
that Yuehai's biggest bottleneck
in development is land shortage.

161
00:06:26,924 --> 00:06:29,205
- We have no land left.
- Do you want the theater or not?

162
00:06:29,404 --> 00:06:31,604
That's why we invited Mr. Xia here

163
00:06:31,604 --> 00:06:33,528
to find a solution

164
00:06:33,528 --> 00:06:35,284
under leader's support.

165
00:06:35,364 --> 00:06:37,005
Look at the mess you've made!

166
00:06:37,005 --> 00:06:38,325
Right. Mr. Tan, calm down.

167
00:06:38,325 --> 00:06:39,085
Don't get angry.

168
00:06:39,125 --> 00:06:40,364
I've got a plan!

169
00:06:40,525 --> 00:06:41,965
I'll withdraw my shares. Okay?

170
00:06:42,525 --> 00:06:43,525
- Me too.
- Me too.

171
00:06:43,565 --> 00:06:44,952
Me too!

172
00:06:44,952 --> 00:06:46,325
No anger or pulse-checks now.

173
00:06:46,325 --> 00:06:48,244
- We're here to solve the problem.
- Invite him back!

174
00:06:48,244 --> 00:06:48,844
Problem solved.

175
00:06:49,205 --> 00:06:50,125
- Are you cornering me?
- Shut up!

176
00:06:50,125 --> 00:06:50,765
Shut up!

177
00:06:50,885 --> 00:06:51,804
Problem solved.

178
00:06:52,085 --> 00:06:53,685
Shut up! Behave.

179
00:06:54,404 --> 00:06:55,885
Sit. Settle down now.

180
00:06:57,724 --> 00:06:59,085
- Just you two are shareholders?
- I...

181
00:06:59,565 --> 00:07:00,724
Only you know what to do?

182
00:07:03,525 --> 00:07:04,885
Aren't you ten united?

183
00:07:05,484 --> 00:07:07,416
Aren't you "perfect ten"?

184
00:07:07,685 --> 00:07:08,325
Forgotten?

185
00:07:09,044 --> 00:07:10,205
Yang Xiaohai hasn't spoken.

186
00:07:11,604 --> 00:07:13,565
Yang Xiaohai, say something.

187
00:07:14,685 --> 00:07:16,164
You're the initiator. You should say.

188
00:07:16,404 --> 00:07:18,724
No, he's just a kid.

189
00:07:19,164 --> 00:07:20,685
Xiaohai, please speak.

190
00:07:23,445 --> 00:07:24,565
Just say something.

191
00:07:28,645 --> 00:07:31,244
Since you insist,
I'll share my thoughts.

192
00:07:33,085 --> 00:07:33,885
First,

193
00:07:35,404 --> 00:07:36,445
I want

194
00:07:36,685 --> 00:07:39,525
to sincerely apologize to everyone.

195
00:07:41,044 --> 00:07:42,044
Apologize for what?

196
00:07:44,164 --> 00:07:45,284
Next, I want to say

197
00:07:46,885 --> 00:07:47,685
that I know

198
00:07:48,724 --> 00:07:50,244
money matters.

199
00:07:50,844 --> 00:07:52,164
But I didn't open the theater

200
00:07:53,284 --> 00:07:54,844
for money.

201
00:07:55,724 --> 00:07:56,565
I love movies,

202
00:07:57,404 --> 00:07:59,685
and I love the community it brings.

203
00:08:00,284 --> 00:08:01,284
Picture this.

204
00:08:03,085 --> 00:08:05,284
Strangers gathering

205
00:08:06,645 --> 00:08:08,804
over one movie and one story,

206
00:08:09,325 --> 00:08:11,325
laughing and crying together,

207
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:13,244
sharing feelings.

208
00:08:14,924 --> 00:08:16,044
Isn't that happy?

209
00:08:17,205 --> 00:08:19,005
I believe that movies

210
00:08:19,484 --> 00:08:22,085
and theaters hold meaning

211
00:08:22,804 --> 00:08:24,085
beyond just profits.

212
00:08:25,685 --> 00:08:28,164
Master, I remember you said

213
00:08:28,765 --> 00:08:31,404
that once we decide to do something,

214
00:08:32,484 --> 00:08:35,685
including business,
be firm and stick to it.

215
00:08:37,004 --> 00:08:38,364
So today, I've made a decision.

216
00:08:39,085 --> 00:08:40,884
Just consider the shares you invested

217
00:08:41,685 --> 00:08:42,925
as a loan from me.

218
00:08:43,764 --> 00:08:45,205
I'll write you an IOU.

219
00:08:46,004 --> 00:08:46,604
In three years,

220
00:08:47,524 --> 00:08:50,364
I'll repay everything with interest.

221
00:08:50,764 --> 00:08:52,604
- I'm here...
- For this theater,

222
00:08:53,644 --> 00:08:55,800
I'll keep running it

223
00:08:56,524 --> 00:08:58,644
according to my original vision.

224
00:09:05,644 --> 00:09:06,244
Move it back.

225
00:09:07,864 --> 00:09:08,884
(No ads in between movies)

226
00:09:08,884 --> 00:09:09,124
Okay.

227
00:09:13,724 --> 00:09:14,805
Mr. Zheng and Ms. Li

228
00:09:14,844 --> 00:09:16,764
have been gone for long with no news.

229
00:09:17,124 --> 00:09:17,884
It's been a week.

230
00:09:20,484 --> 00:09:22,604
What do you think they're doing?

231
00:09:23,045 --> 00:09:23,805
Who knows?

232
00:09:24,524 --> 00:09:26,644
Tomorrow is the county reporting day.

233
00:09:26,805 --> 00:09:28,445
Get the quarterly report ready.

234
00:09:28,965 --> 00:09:29,524
I'll go.

235
00:09:31,205 --> 00:09:31,884
What for?

236
00:09:32,085 --> 00:09:32,965
You know the reason.

237
00:09:33,364 --> 00:09:34,244
Work can't be delayed.

238
00:09:34,565 --> 00:09:35,565
I'll do the reporting.

239
00:09:37,085 --> 00:09:38,805
Fine. I don't want to argue with you.

240
00:09:39,965 --> 00:09:41,205
I'll go with you.

241
00:09:41,445 --> 00:09:42,325
If

242
00:09:42,445 --> 00:09:45,244
Mr. Xia asks for details of the report,
you won't be able to answer.

243
00:09:45,484 --> 00:09:47,205
No need. You go by yourself.

244
00:09:47,484 --> 00:09:49,205
Or bring Lin Tofu to take photos.

245
00:09:49,685 --> 00:09:51,925
Do you even know
where County Committee Compound is?

246
00:09:51,925 --> 00:09:53,484
I can ask for directions.

247
00:09:53,764 --> 00:09:54,685
None of you need to go.

248
00:09:55,484 --> 00:09:56,925
They are returning today.

249
00:09:58,165 --> 00:09:59,884
- Why not say it earlier?
- How did you know?

250
00:10:03,325 --> 00:10:05,325
He called yesterday and I answered.

251
00:10:06,045 --> 00:10:07,724
What did he say? Where did they go?

252
00:10:07,724 --> 00:10:08,472
What did he say?

253
00:10:08,805 --> 00:10:09,565
Don't you know?

254
00:10:10,764 --> 00:10:12,364
You've learned bad habits from Mr. Tan.

255
00:10:12,364 --> 00:10:13,965
Alright. Don't interrupt.

256
00:10:14,004 --> 00:10:15,085
What exactly did he say?

257
00:10:15,925 --> 00:10:16,405
He said

258
00:10:17,364 --> 00:10:18,840
they'll announce a major decision

259
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:20,685
that will determine Yuehai's future.

260
00:10:25,085 --> 00:10:27,844
Leaders! Mr. Zheng and Ms. Li are back.

261
00:10:28,124 --> 00:10:29,644
Everyone to the meeting room now.

262
00:10:34,244 --> 00:10:35,085
Let's go.

263
00:10:35,764 --> 00:10:36,124
Well...

264
00:10:36,764 --> 00:10:37,445
Mr. Zheng!

265
00:10:37,764 --> 00:10:38,484
Ms. Li!

266
00:11:01,004 --> 00:11:01,720
You're all here.

267
00:11:03,724 --> 00:11:04,884
Let me introduce everyone.

268
00:11:06,364 --> 00:11:09,205
This is senior engineer Qi Shimin,
from the Aviation Survey

269
00:11:09,524 --> 00:11:10,424
and Design Institute.

270
00:11:10,685 --> 00:11:12,085
You can call him Mr. Qi.

271
00:11:13,004 --> 00:11:15,405
These are Yuehai's other Town Mayors,

272
00:11:16,085 --> 00:11:16,764
Mr. Lin,

273
00:11:17,165 --> 00:11:17,925
Mr. Xie,

274
00:11:18,205 --> 00:11:18,925
and Mr. Tan.

275
00:11:21,445 --> 00:11:22,004
Hello, Mr. Qi.

276
00:11:25,965 --> 00:11:27,405
Hello, I'm Tan Guangming.

277
00:11:28,644 --> 00:11:30,724
Look at yourselves.

278
00:11:31,205 --> 00:11:32,045
We came in a rush.

279
00:11:32,724 --> 00:11:34,328
Right. Don't blame them.

280
00:11:34,484 --> 00:11:35,604
We called them suddenly.

281
00:11:35,604 --> 00:11:36,724
Mr. Zheng, Ms. Li.

282
00:11:37,004 --> 00:11:39,445
You've been gone for a whole week.

283
00:11:40,484 --> 00:11:42,724
And you come back bringing an Einstein.

284
00:11:43,565 --> 00:11:45,244
We were worried.

285
00:11:47,445 --> 00:11:48,484
Please don't mind.

286
00:11:49,325 --> 00:11:50,244
Introductions are done.

287
00:11:50,244 --> 00:11:51,764
Let's start the meeting.

288
00:11:52,805 --> 00:11:53,244
Sit down.

289
00:11:53,565 --> 00:11:54,205
- Okay.
- Sit.

290
00:11:54,405 --> 00:11:55,085
Sit down.

291
00:11:56,165 --> 00:11:57,805
Here, Mr. Lin.

292
00:12:00,965 --> 00:12:01,965
Xie, meeting starts.

293
00:12:03,484 --> 00:12:04,565
He's the guest. Sit.

294
00:12:04,685 --> 00:12:05,285
Hurry, sit.

295
00:12:07,805 --> 00:12:08,484
Well...

296
00:12:09,965 --> 00:12:10,724
As everyone knows,

297
00:12:11,524 --> 00:12:12,884
what Yuehai lacks right now

298
00:12:14,124 --> 00:12:14,524
is land.

299
00:12:15,325 --> 00:12:15,925
Without land,

300
00:12:16,325 --> 00:12:19,045
our future plans are castles in the air.

301
00:12:20,165 --> 00:12:22,604
Mr. Qi is an expert in this field.

302
00:12:23,244 --> 00:12:24,925
Ms. Li and I invited him here

303
00:12:25,644 --> 00:12:27,805
to see if we can launch

304
00:12:28,124 --> 00:12:30,205
a land expansion project in Yuehai.

305
00:12:31,124 --> 00:12:31,896
Mr. Zheng.

306
00:12:32,728 --> 00:12:34,285
It's not a launch, but an inspection.

307
00:12:35,445 --> 00:12:38,124
To assess whether Yuehai
has the capability

308
00:12:38,264 --> 00:12:38,925
to do it.

309
00:12:39,565 --> 00:12:41,884
Right. My wording wasn't precise.

310
00:12:44,165 --> 00:12:44,884
What do you mean?

311
00:12:45,604 --> 00:12:48,405
John B. Herbich's 1990 publication,

312
00:12:48,405 --> 00:12:50,205
Handbook of Coastal
and Ocean Engineering,

313
00:12:50,604 --> 00:12:52,054
Robert M. Sorensen's

314
00:12:52,054 --> 00:12:53,688
publication in 1978,

315
00:12:53,688 --> 00:12:54,840
Coastal Engineering,

316
00:12:56,644 --> 00:12:59,484
Peter Nielsen's 1992 publication,

317
00:13:00,124 --> 00:13:02,285
Coastal Bottom Boundary Layers
and Sediment Transport,

318
00:13:02,644 --> 00:13:05,285
and my 1988 doctoral thesis,

319
00:13:05,524 --> 00:13:09,685
Analysis of Geotechnical Problems
In Land Reclamation.

320
00:13:10,484 --> 00:13:11,685
Most of your questions

321
00:13:11,685 --> 00:13:14,405
can be answered in those works.

322
00:13:16,724 --> 00:13:18,484
You don't have to switch

323
00:13:18,724 --> 00:13:19,925
between Chinese and English.

324
00:13:20,285 --> 00:13:23,032
Mr. Xie, what Mr. Qi said

325
00:13:23,205 --> 00:13:24,805
were just names and paper titles.

326
00:13:25,364 --> 00:13:26,484
I know.

327
00:13:26,484 --> 00:13:27,405
I didn't mean anything.

328
00:13:27,685 --> 00:13:29,400
Though capable,
you never talk like that.

329
00:13:29,484 --> 00:13:29,884
Why...

330
00:13:30,364 --> 00:13:30,925
What's up?

331
00:13:31,285 --> 00:13:33,524
I have a question, Mr. Qi.

332
00:13:35,764 --> 00:13:36,244
Go ahead.

333
00:13:36,644 --> 00:13:37,560
Roughly how much

334
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:39,685
would a project like this cost?

335
00:13:40,445 --> 00:13:42,004
Cost isn't my concern.

336
00:13:42,244 --> 00:13:43,524
I just solve technical problems.

337
00:13:43,844 --> 00:13:44,565
I know.

338
00:13:44,805 --> 00:13:46,805
But you must have an estimate, right?

339
00:13:46,884 --> 00:13:48,325
As an expert, you can estimate it.

340
00:13:48,484 --> 00:13:50,445
I know that millions won't be enough.

341
00:13:50,445 --> 00:13:51,644
Got to be tens of millions.

342
00:13:52,244 --> 00:13:53,524
There's a figure, right?

343
00:13:56,685 --> 00:13:59,604
Ms. Li, I think Yuehai

344
00:14:00,244 --> 00:14:03,165
is not ready
for the land expansion project yet.

345
00:14:04,364 --> 00:14:05,165
What does he mean?

346
00:14:07,724 --> 00:14:08,454
Mr. Qi.

347
00:14:08,664 --> 00:14:11,124
When you first went
to the Netherlands for training,

348
00:14:11,405 --> 00:14:12,965
you didn't know a word of Dutch.

349
00:14:13,685 --> 00:14:15,604
But look at how skilled you are now.

350
00:14:18,004 --> 00:14:20,524
You... You two.

351
00:14:21,124 --> 00:14:22,205
What are you saying?

352
00:14:23,045 --> 00:14:23,925
I can't understand.

353
00:14:24,965 --> 00:14:26,405
W-What's your relationship?

354
00:14:27,604 --> 00:14:29,325
What's that has to do with you?

355
00:14:29,724 --> 00:14:30,165
Sit down.

356
00:14:31,405 --> 00:14:31,965
I'll explain.

357
00:14:33,405 --> 00:14:35,045
Tan, here's the thing.

358
00:14:35,484 --> 00:14:37,244
Mr. Qi told me before

359
00:14:37,724 --> 00:14:40,165
that for a project of this scale,

360
00:14:40,325 --> 00:14:41,848
it would require

361
00:14:42,345 --> 00:14:43,925
at least 150 million.

362
00:14:47,604 --> 00:14:48,925
At least 150 million.

363
00:14:49,724 --> 00:14:50,872
So there is a number.

364
00:14:52,524 --> 00:14:54,165
Mr. Tan, we'll discuss the money

365
00:14:54,565 --> 00:14:56,152
after Mr. Qi finishes the survey

366
00:14:56,244 --> 00:14:58,764
and gives an accurate project quote.

367
00:14:59,085 --> 00:14:59,685
Okay.

368
00:15:00,205 --> 00:15:00,565
Right.

369
00:15:01,685 --> 00:15:03,445
We'll talk about it later.

370
00:15:03,884 --> 00:15:05,644
Based on the specific situation.

371
00:15:06,445 --> 00:15:07,685
Now the priority is...

372
00:15:08,004 --> 00:15:10,616
Lin, put aside

373
00:15:10,616 --> 00:15:11,925
your current work.

374
00:15:12,124 --> 00:15:15,124
Take Mr. Qi to investigate every day

375
00:15:16,085 --> 00:15:18,244
to find a suitable location.

376
00:15:18,644 --> 00:15:21,124
Once found, we can start
the application process.

377
00:15:25,165 --> 00:15:26,285
Are you listening to me?

378
00:15:29,165 --> 00:15:30,205
Oh, I remember.

379
00:15:31,604 --> 00:15:32,565
I know you.

380
00:15:35,045 --> 00:15:35,884
You know me?

381
00:15:36,364 --> 00:15:38,884
Then, your expertise
is better than I thought.

382
00:15:39,205 --> 00:15:41,724
You... Qi Stone?

383
00:15:45,565 --> 00:15:47,764
Are you Qi Stone?

384
00:15:47,925 --> 00:15:48,724
Who?

385
00:15:49,085 --> 00:15:49,884
- Stone?
- Well...

386
00:15:50,244 --> 00:15:52,644
Mr. Qi is Ms. Li's university classmate.

387
00:15:52,644 --> 00:15:54,456
He had a crush on Ms. Li,

388
00:15:55,124 --> 00:15:57,285
but didn't dare to confess.

389
00:15:58,004 --> 00:16:00,604
So he turned into stone
when he saw Ms. Li.

390
00:16:00,644 --> 00:16:02,364
So, Qi Stone.

391
00:16:03,604 --> 00:16:04,925
So...

392
00:16:05,565 --> 00:16:06,565
You are so familiar.

393
00:16:07,844 --> 00:16:09,965
Well, we're all friends here.

394
00:16:10,364 --> 00:16:12,925
Come on, Mr. Stone.

395
00:16:14,884 --> 00:16:15,364
A stone now.

396
00:16:17,484 --> 00:16:19,004
So that's how it is.

397
00:16:36,364 --> 00:16:36,805
Lin.

398
00:16:37,445 --> 00:16:37,805
Tan.

399
00:16:37,965 --> 00:16:38,445
Busy?

400
00:16:38,565 --> 00:16:39,124
Yes. Sit.

401
00:16:42,405 --> 00:16:43,800
Still busy

402
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:46,004
with the land reclamation project?

403
00:16:48,124 --> 00:16:49,004
Tan, let me tell you.

404
00:16:49,045 --> 00:16:51,325
These days, Mr. Qi and I have walked

405
00:16:52,484 --> 00:16:54,844
all over the beaches of Yuehai.

406
00:16:55,565 --> 00:16:57,405
I just wanted to ask...

407
00:16:57,656 --> 00:16:59,352
So, the past few days,

408
00:16:59,484 --> 00:17:01,364
have you found a location?

409
00:17:01,565 --> 00:17:02,085
Not yet.

410
00:17:03,285 --> 00:17:04,044
But soon.

411
00:17:09,004 --> 00:17:11,405
Mr. Qi is really remarkable.

412
00:17:12,524 --> 00:17:13,965
When I saw him

413
00:17:13,965 --> 00:17:15,324
at the first sight,

414
00:17:15,605 --> 00:17:17,365
I thought he only knew theory,

415
00:17:17,724 --> 00:17:19,405
and had no field experience.

416
00:17:19,405 --> 00:17:19,925
Is that so?

417
00:17:20,885 --> 00:17:22,044
But these days, I've known

418
00:17:22,044 --> 00:17:24,084
that he's worked
on countless major projects.

419
00:17:24,645 --> 00:17:26,712
He knows construction details
better than I do.

420
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:29,592
I've never seen anyone

421
00:17:29,592 --> 00:17:30,965
as smart as him.

422
00:17:31,845 --> 00:17:33,764
Lin, I just want to ask.

423
00:17:34,324 --> 00:17:36,125
You've put in so much effort

424
00:17:36,125 --> 00:17:38,044
and still haven't found a suitable spot,

425
00:17:38,284 --> 00:17:38,885
doesn't it mean

426
00:17:39,004 --> 00:17:41,724
the project might not be feasible?

427
00:17:42,324 --> 00:17:43,804
No. Look.

428
00:17:44,165 --> 00:17:44,724
Listen.

429
00:17:47,324 --> 00:17:49,048
The key issue now is

430
00:17:49,048 --> 00:17:50,488
whether we can find in Yuehai

431
00:17:51,244 --> 00:17:54,165
the right geological conditions
for the project.

432
00:17:54,324 --> 00:17:56,445
So we must first

433
00:17:56,445 --> 00:17:58,645
find the right geological conditions,
right?

434
00:17:58,804 --> 00:17:59,125
Right.

435
00:17:59,205 --> 00:18:01,445
But you haven't found it.

436
00:18:01,564 --> 00:18:01,965
We will.

437
00:18:02,524 --> 00:18:03,096
Okay.

438
00:18:03,244 --> 00:18:05,084
And the second issue is the high cost.

439
00:18:05,324 --> 00:18:07,352
High cost means more money.

440
00:18:07,564 --> 00:18:09,912
Well, since Yuehai was built,

441
00:18:10,004 --> 00:18:12,685
it has been developing fast.

442
00:18:12,685 --> 00:18:13,575
It never stopped.

443
00:18:13,575 --> 00:18:14,965
It keeps developing,

444
00:18:15,244 --> 00:18:17,484
so we don't have much money left.

445
00:18:17,804 --> 00:18:19,365
Remember what Mr. Qi said?

446
00:18:20,044 --> 00:18:21,685
It will cost at least 150 million yuan.

447
00:18:21,804 --> 00:18:22,764
I found it very strange.

448
00:18:23,044 --> 00:18:24,084
How could you and Xie

449
00:18:24,084 --> 00:18:26,365
have no reaction to 150 million yuan?

450
00:18:26,645 --> 00:18:29,524
We don't have that much money.
We can only borrow from the bank.

451
00:18:29,724 --> 00:18:31,845
But the bank might not lend it.
Even if it does lend,

452
00:18:31,965 --> 00:18:34,104
how do we pay back 150 million?

453
00:18:34,575 --> 00:18:35,044
Right?

454
00:18:35,605 --> 00:18:38,004
Mr. Zheng and Ms. Li
will deal with the money issue.

455
00:18:38,405 --> 00:18:40,764
I only care
if it's technically feasible.

456
00:18:41,205 --> 00:18:43,480
Lin, I think
you're being too optimistic.

457
00:18:44,284 --> 00:18:45,484
Come. You just

458
00:18:46,165 --> 00:18:49,125
lack some background knowledge.

459
00:18:49,524 --> 00:18:50,484
I suggest, come here,

460
00:18:50,605 --> 00:18:52,125
- Wait...
- You should read

461
00:18:52,365 --> 00:18:53,804
these books Mr. Qi recommended.

462
00:18:54,165 --> 00:18:55,064
Why should I do that?

463
00:18:55,165 --> 00:18:56,764
Then you won't have these doubts.

464
00:18:57,084 --> 00:18:57,445
Here.

465
00:18:57,524 --> 00:18:58,232
I have no doubts.

466
00:18:58,232 --> 00:18:59,896
We're not talking about the same thing.

467
00:19:00,044 --> 00:19:02,040
I mean, if there's no money,

468
00:19:02,324 --> 00:19:04,804
how can you implement
those technical details?

469
00:19:05,044 --> 00:19:06,648
You're putting the
cart before the horse.

470
00:19:06,925 --> 00:19:08,365
Trust Mr. Zheng and Ms. Li.

471
00:19:08,845 --> 00:19:10,405
They won't do anything unrealistic.

472
00:19:10,712 --> 00:19:11,262
You...

473
00:19:13,885 --> 00:19:15,484
Fine, sorry to disturb you.

474
00:19:26,324 --> 00:19:27,845
Taking a bath.

475
00:19:50,724 --> 00:19:51,352
Coming.

476
00:19:51,992 --> 00:19:52,760
Coming.

477
00:19:53,484 --> 00:19:55,804
- Mr. Xie, what's up?
- Try it. The water's too hot.

478
00:19:58,804 --> 00:19:59,925
I added too much hot water.

479
00:20:00,792 --> 00:20:02,524
Sorry, I'll add some hot...
No, cold water.

480
00:20:02,925 --> 00:20:03,605
Wait a minute.

481
00:20:09,405 --> 00:20:09,912
Not hot?

482
00:20:10,324 --> 00:20:10,885
You're here.

483
00:20:12,205 --> 00:20:13,925
Actually, it's hot.

484
00:20:19,764 --> 00:20:20,484
Here.

485
00:20:21,564 --> 00:20:22,484
Let me see.

486
00:20:23,605 --> 00:20:24,605
What's going on?

487
00:20:25,484 --> 00:20:26,284
Anything happens?

488
00:20:28,044 --> 00:20:29,205
Tell me about it.

489
00:20:29,284 --> 00:20:30,685
I'll fix it for you.

490
00:20:31,165 --> 00:20:33,405
Mr. Qi, it really is that saying.

491
00:20:33,645 --> 00:20:35,405
After searching far and wide,

492
00:20:35,605 --> 00:20:37,804
persistence finally paid off.

493
00:20:38,764 --> 00:20:39,564
Xie, you're here.

494
00:20:40,125 --> 00:20:41,084
So, did you found it?

495
00:20:42,405 --> 00:20:43,605
It's been confirmed.

496
00:20:44,084 --> 00:20:44,605
Mr. Lin.

497
00:20:45,605 --> 00:20:47,724
The soil sample test results
haven't come out.

498
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:50,155
But based on my experience,

499
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:51,244
it should be fine.

500
00:20:52,804 --> 00:20:53,205
Look!

501
00:20:56,004 --> 00:20:56,724
Where is it?

502
00:20:58,165 --> 00:21:00,445
Well, can I say it?

503
00:21:01,965 --> 00:21:02,365
Go ahead.

504
00:21:03,724 --> 00:21:05,976
It's at Snail Bay.

505
00:21:12,724 --> 00:21:14,324
Snail Bay is on Binhai Road, right?

506
00:21:16,804 --> 00:21:17,324
Well...

507
00:21:18,205 --> 00:21:21,165
Mr. Qi said the test results

508
00:21:21,564 --> 00:21:22,524
aren't out yet.

509
00:21:22,685 --> 00:21:25,165
It might not be on the Binhai Road.

510
00:21:25,405 --> 00:21:26,524
Don't overthink it.

511
00:21:27,324 --> 00:21:28,524
Okay?

512
00:21:43,244 --> 00:21:45,324
Xie, you are leaving?

513
00:21:51,576 --> 00:21:53,165
Xie, take your clothes on!

514
00:21:57,240 --> 00:21:58,872
(Chunmei Printery)

515
00:22:07,165 --> 00:22:07,605
Dad.

516
00:22:09,605 --> 00:22:10,004
Dad.

517
00:22:11,445 --> 00:22:11,925
Dad!

518
00:22:13,205 --> 00:22:13,724
Dad!

519
00:22:40,324 --> 00:22:43,125
The sea breeze carries distant longing.

520
00:22:43,885 --> 00:22:46,524
The outline of home
is swept away by the sea.

521
00:22:48,044 --> 00:22:49,885
Darkness is about to surge.

522
00:22:52,645 --> 00:22:53,848
Oh, sea!

523
00:22:54,328 --> 00:22:56,284
Please swallow my home.

524
00:22:58,125 --> 00:22:59,165
Swallow your home?

525
00:23:01,125 --> 00:23:01,965
Your life is good.

526
00:23:03,724 --> 00:23:04,685
Why swallow your home?

527
00:23:06,845 --> 00:23:08,965
Isn't my poem good?

528
00:23:09,484 --> 00:23:12,524
I wrote it by myself.
My night school teacher said,

529
00:23:12,605 --> 00:23:13,720
- The teacher's wrong.
- "Everyone can..."

530
00:23:13,885 --> 00:23:17,244
Don't listen to that.
Everyone can? If so, it'd be chaos!

531
00:23:17,645 --> 00:23:19,445
Stop talking that nonsense.

532
00:23:35,804 --> 00:23:36,724
You're so young.

533
00:23:38,724 --> 00:23:40,764
Why so depressing?

534
00:23:41,645 --> 00:23:44,165
Be more positive.

535
00:23:45,564 --> 00:23:47,764
Look at me.
So many things to deal with every day.

536
00:23:48,804 --> 00:23:50,205
I'm still doing well, right?

537
00:23:52,205 --> 00:23:53,284
It's really no big deal.

538
00:23:53,284 --> 00:23:53,925
Right?

539
00:24:00,084 --> 00:24:01,885
- Dad, what's wrong with your mouth?
- Nothing.

540
00:24:02,804 --> 00:24:04,645
Well, you're stressed, aren't you?

541
00:24:05,244 --> 00:24:06,084
No.

542
00:24:06,484 --> 00:24:07,484
Are you really okay?

543
00:24:07,524 --> 00:24:08,324
Stressed?

544
00:24:08,885 --> 00:24:10,776
I've been through storms in life.

545
00:24:11,205 --> 00:24:11,925
I won't be.

546
00:24:21,752 --> 00:24:23,244
Is your mom doing well at home?

547
00:24:23,925 --> 00:24:24,484
Is she okay?

548
00:24:25,804 --> 00:24:27,244
She's fine. Really.

549
00:24:32,284 --> 00:24:32,605
Dad.

550
00:24:33,724 --> 00:24:35,448
I just saw you

551
00:24:35,448 --> 00:24:36,764
pass by.

552
00:24:37,605 --> 00:24:38,840
You didn't acknowledge me.

553
00:24:40,885 --> 00:24:42,244
Are you going home today?

554
00:25:10,324 --> 00:25:13,044
(After confirming the site and area,)

555
00:25:13,564 --> 00:25:15,244
(and finishing the approval procedures,)

556
00:25:15,885 --> 00:25:17,845
(the land reclamation project
was approved.)

557
00:25:19,365 --> 00:25:21,125
(But just as construction
was about to begin,)

558
00:25:22,205 --> 00:25:25,165
(a new problem emerged.)

559
00:25:26,165 --> 00:25:28,088
Must we demolish
the factories on Binhai Road?

560
00:25:31,605 --> 00:25:34,524
Mr. Zheng, the report is very clear.

561
00:25:35,125 --> 00:25:37,484
The factories on Binhai Road
are too close to the shore.

562
00:25:38,165 --> 00:25:40,044
If we want to proceed,
they must be removed.

563
00:25:42,004 --> 00:25:43,605
Our coastline is long.

564
00:25:43,965 --> 00:25:45,205
Can't we choose another place?

565
00:25:45,804 --> 00:25:48,165
You know very well
the significance of Binhai Road.

566
00:25:48,564 --> 00:25:49,885
We fought tooth and nail

567
00:25:50,165 --> 00:25:52,484
to reclaim it from the cadres.

568
00:25:52,885 --> 00:25:53,845
Now we demolish it.

569
00:25:54,564 --> 00:25:55,965
How can I explain to those owners?

570
00:25:58,004 --> 00:25:59,925
Let's think of another way, okay?

571
00:26:01,564 --> 00:26:03,445
There is a way. Of course there is.

572
00:26:04,445 --> 00:26:04,965
See?

573
00:26:05,645 --> 00:26:07,845
That's why experts are experts.

574
00:26:08,244 --> 00:26:10,044
There must be another way, right?

575
00:26:10,845 --> 00:26:11,484
Give up.

576
00:26:13,564 --> 00:26:16,152
If there's so much trouble,
we might as well drop it.

577
00:26:16,564 --> 00:26:19,448
We can't give up.

578
00:26:19,764 --> 00:26:21,484
We must do it. But...

579
00:26:23,205 --> 00:26:23,985
Ms. Li.

580
00:26:24,472 --> 00:26:26,524
Please arrange a car
to take me to the station.

581
00:26:26,804 --> 00:26:27,804
I'll return to Beijing.

582
00:26:27,804 --> 00:26:28,524
You're leaving?

583
00:26:28,724 --> 00:26:31,605
Yes. Wasting my time is wasting my life.

584
00:26:31,804 --> 00:26:33,284
I've written the report.

585
00:26:33,484 --> 00:26:35,205
Submit it or not, you decide.

586
00:26:36,524 --> 00:26:38,205
Mr. Qi.

587
00:26:43,524 --> 00:26:45,560
Mr. Zheng, don't hesitate.

588
00:26:46,244 --> 00:26:48,084
If you're worried
Binhai Road can't be cleared,

589
00:26:48,524 --> 00:26:49,564
I'll talk to them.

590
00:26:55,084 --> 00:26:55,484
Submit it.

591
00:26:56,685 --> 00:26:58,296
What do you mean?

592
00:26:58,445 --> 00:27:00,125
Why only demolish Binhai Road?

593
00:27:01,284 --> 00:27:02,445
Only Road 1 and Road 2?

594
00:27:02,445 --> 00:27:02,724
Hi.

595
00:27:02,724 --> 00:27:03,845
Why not Road 3?

596
00:27:04,605 --> 00:27:06,885
They think we "monkeys"
are easy to push around?

597
00:27:07,324 --> 00:27:07,965
Exactly.

598
00:27:08,044 --> 00:27:08,965
- This is bullying.
- Yeah.

599
00:27:09,044 --> 00:27:09,965
Right.

600
00:27:11,044 --> 00:27:13,084
We came here with Mr. Zheng

601
00:27:13,244 --> 00:27:14,804
when the town is first built.

602
00:27:15,685 --> 00:27:17,645
Now they burn the bridge
after cross the river.

603
00:27:17,885 --> 00:27:18,925
Right.

604
00:27:18,965 --> 00:27:19,724
All these years...

605
00:27:21,165 --> 00:27:22,845
I'm telling the truth.

606
00:27:23,925 --> 00:27:24,564
To be honest,

607
00:27:25,445 --> 00:27:27,845
I had someone divine the luck
for my land.

608
00:27:27,845 --> 00:27:29,804
I paid triple the price to get it back.

609
00:27:30,125 --> 00:27:31,288
There's no way I'll agree

610
00:27:31,288 --> 00:27:32,324
to demolish it.

611
00:27:32,605 --> 00:27:35,484
Ever since I moved to Binhai Road,
my business's gotten better.

612
00:27:36,365 --> 00:27:38,424
It's true. Binhai Road

613
00:27:38,424 --> 00:27:39,524
is a blessed place for us.

614
00:27:39,764 --> 00:27:41,205
Yes, it's an auspicious location.

615
00:27:41,205 --> 00:27:42,200
After we moved there,

616
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:43,165
things get better.

617
00:27:43,165 --> 00:27:43,608
Right.

618
00:27:46,724 --> 00:27:47,244
Xuemei.

619
00:27:48,764 --> 00:27:50,724
You're the head
of our Printing Association.

620
00:27:51,845 --> 00:27:54,724
What do you think about it?
We'll listen to you, right?

621
00:27:55,125 --> 00:27:55,724
- Right.
- Right.

622
00:27:56,004 --> 00:27:56,885
Well, Xuemei.

623
00:27:57,165 --> 00:27:58,244
Your business is large.

624
00:27:58,445 --> 00:27:59,724
But we small owners

625
00:27:59,965 --> 00:28:01,685
rely on these businesses to survive.

626
00:28:01,885 --> 00:28:02,328
Right?

627
00:28:02,484 --> 00:28:03,044
Yes.

628
00:28:03,044 --> 00:28:04,165
Everyone, calm down.

629
00:28:05,004 --> 00:28:07,645
When we came,
we paid the city construction fee.

630
00:28:08,125 --> 00:28:09,965
And we got the land use certificates.

631
00:28:10,605 --> 00:28:12,764
But the land doesn't belong to us.

632
00:28:12,925 --> 00:28:14,524
If the town government insists,

633
00:28:15,284 --> 00:28:16,044
we have no choice.

634
00:28:16,845 --> 00:28:17,484
What do we do?

635
00:28:17,965 --> 00:28:18,524
Exactly.

636
00:28:18,804 --> 00:28:21,784
Well, Xuemei, should we just wait
and do nothing?

637
00:28:21,885 --> 00:28:23,645
Just wait to be demolished, is that it?

638
00:28:24,205 --> 00:28:26,244
- Let me finish.
- What's the rush? Let her finish.

639
00:28:26,244 --> 00:28:27,484
Just let me finish.

640
00:28:28,244 --> 00:28:29,845
The land doesn't belong to us.

641
00:28:30,445 --> 00:28:31,324
But the buildings

642
00:28:31,804 --> 00:28:33,324
are built by us.

643
00:28:34,084 --> 00:28:36,244
We don't get to decide
whether they're torn down,

644
00:28:36,484 --> 00:28:37,564
so we won't debate it.

645
00:28:37,965 --> 00:28:39,645
But we do get to negotiate

646
00:28:40,484 --> 00:28:43,284
fair compensation.

647
00:28:44,044 --> 00:28:44,965
Compensation?

648
00:28:45,165 --> 00:28:47,205
I told you not to rush.

649
00:28:47,445 --> 00:28:48,764
Look at all of you.

650
00:28:50,724 --> 00:28:53,365
Xuemei, you have the clearest head.

651
00:28:54,365 --> 00:28:57,324
Well, you're the head.
We'll all listen to you.

652
00:28:57,885 --> 00:28:59,165
Right, listen to Ms. Gao.

653
00:28:59,165 --> 00:29:00,084
Listen to Xuemei.

654
00:29:00,605 --> 00:29:01,528
Come on, sit over here.

655
00:29:01,528 --> 00:29:03,004
- Let's discuss.
- Come on.

656
00:29:03,044 --> 00:29:04,044
Let's have a meeting.

657
00:29:04,044 --> 00:29:04,685
Push the tables.

658
00:29:04,724 --> 00:29:05,724
Push the tables together.

659
00:29:06,445 --> 00:29:07,284
Here, push it over.

660
00:29:07,524 --> 00:29:07,885
Here.

661
00:29:08,165 --> 00:29:10,685
Ms. Gao, that's the situation.

662
00:29:11,125 --> 00:29:13,564
Honestly, we don't want
to demolish Binhai Road either.

663
00:29:14,445 --> 00:29:16,205
But for Yuehai's development,

664
00:29:16,724 --> 00:29:18,405
we have no choice.

665
00:29:21,004 --> 00:29:23,284
Since it must be done, we agree.

666
00:29:24,004 --> 00:29:25,528
But the compensation must be fair.

667
00:29:25,804 --> 00:29:28,205
We held a meeting about this.

668
00:29:28,685 --> 00:29:30,845
300,000 yuan for each plot.

669
00:29:32,405 --> 00:29:35,244
The demolition involves
over 100 factories.

670
00:29:35,724 --> 00:29:37,125
That's over 50 million yuan.

671
00:29:38,004 --> 00:29:39,885
This price isn't decided casually.

672
00:29:40,125 --> 00:29:41,724
It's based on market value.

673
00:29:43,724 --> 00:29:46,324
What if I offer 608,000 yuan per plot?

674
00:29:50,044 --> 00:29:51,004
Only 8,000 yuan, right?

675
00:29:52,365 --> 00:29:54,965
8,000 yuan can be paid immediately
as relocation support.

676
00:29:55,084 --> 00:29:58,004
After the project finishes,
you rebuild in the same location.

677
00:29:58,564 --> 00:30:00,324
I'll give you twice the area you had.

678
00:30:02,804 --> 00:30:03,685
What do you think?

679
00:30:04,925 --> 00:30:07,764
What I think doesn't matter.
It's not just my place being demolished.

680
00:30:08,044 --> 00:30:10,724
I can't make this decision for them.

681
00:30:11,084 --> 00:30:12,965
Everyone's situation is different.

682
00:30:13,284 --> 00:30:15,564
You'll have to talk with each of them.

683
00:30:18,084 --> 00:30:19,885
Have you decided? Moving or not?

684
00:30:20,365 --> 00:30:22,524
My mom let us move in with her
after the demolition.

685
00:30:22,724 --> 00:30:24,965
Then I'd be a live-in son-in-law.
No way!

686
00:30:25,405 --> 00:30:27,324
I don't want to serve your mom
at your home.

687
00:30:27,685 --> 00:30:28,645
What's wrong with that?

688
00:30:28,645 --> 00:30:30,685
- If you don't want, just split up!
- You dare hit me?

689
00:30:30,885 --> 00:30:31,845
You hit me!

690
00:30:31,925 --> 00:30:33,324
- Stop!
- Have you wanted out of this for long?

691
00:30:33,324 --> 00:30:35,084
Ms. Li, stay out of it. Let her hit.

692
00:30:35,084 --> 00:30:35,685
- What can she do?
- Right?

693
00:30:35,724 --> 00:30:36,564
I am hitting you!

694
00:30:36,724 --> 00:30:38,205
You two can argue at home.

695
00:30:40,645 --> 00:30:41,244
You are...

696
00:30:42,804 --> 00:30:44,804
Meng! Come here! Hurry!

697
00:30:46,724 --> 00:30:47,165
Come on.

698
00:30:48,004 --> 00:30:49,764
We plan to start construction here,

699
00:30:50,205 --> 00:30:52,125
so we have to demolish the buildings.

700
00:30:52,445 --> 00:30:54,244
- And the cement...
- Qingtian, got any shrimp paste?

701
00:30:56,845 --> 00:30:58,885
Well, I'll get you some later.

702
00:30:59,004 --> 00:30:59,925
Let me finish first.

703
00:31:00,205 --> 00:31:01,784
You're close to Xuemei.

704
00:31:01,784 --> 00:31:03,000
Don't you know I don't smoke?

705
00:31:03,084 --> 00:31:03,925
Come on, sit.

706
00:31:04,125 --> 00:31:05,284
Take your time.

707
00:31:05,605 --> 00:31:07,165
Take your time. This is inevitable.

708
00:31:07,524 --> 00:31:08,824
- You get along with Xuemei.
- Yeah, it's okay.

709
00:31:08,824 --> 00:31:09,656
You can understand.

710
00:31:09,656 --> 00:31:10,804
- Take a deep breath.
- What I'm saying...

711
00:31:11,032 --> 00:31:11,764
Slow down.

712
00:31:12,125 --> 00:31:12,645
No rush.

713
00:31:12,645 --> 00:31:14,724
It's good for you.
You don't have loss. Don't cry.

714
00:31:14,724 --> 00:31:16,084
The clinic is over there.

715
00:31:16,084 --> 00:31:17,016
Let me check you out.

716
00:31:17,484 --> 00:31:17,965
Alright.

717
00:31:18,044 --> 00:31:18,804
I'm fine now.

718
00:31:19,645 --> 00:31:20,165
I'm fine.

719
00:31:20,244 --> 00:31:20,645
Really?

720
00:31:20,645 --> 00:31:21,685
No need. Thank you.

721
00:31:21,885 --> 00:31:22,845
Don't leave!

722
00:31:22,872 --> 00:31:23,885
We're going too far?

723
00:31:24,125 --> 00:31:25,004
I think you are.

724
00:31:25,205 --> 00:31:26,845
You're wasting state funds.

725
00:31:26,845 --> 00:31:27,445
Hold on.

726
00:31:27,445 --> 00:31:28,244
That's ridiculous.

727
00:31:28,284 --> 00:31:29,080
Say it clearly.

728
00:31:29,405 --> 00:31:31,205
How am I wasting state funds?

729
00:31:31,365 --> 00:31:32,324
We're building things!

730
00:31:32,324 --> 00:31:33,044
I don't get it.

731
00:31:33,044 --> 00:31:33,925
- I don't understand.
- Wait...

732
00:31:33,965 --> 00:31:35,640
We hired the country's top experts!

733
00:31:36,764 --> 00:31:39,605
Excellent! Tear it down!

734
00:31:40,165 --> 00:31:41,400
I give it my full agreement!

735
00:31:41,880 --> 00:31:44,004
Anyway,
I'm moving to Shanghai next month.

736
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:45,167
Okay.

737
00:31:45,205 --> 00:31:46,125
Mr. Lin, I want to ask.

738
00:31:46,524 --> 00:31:49,154
How much compensation will I get?

739
00:31:49,154 --> 00:31:49,624
Alright.

740
00:31:49,804 --> 00:31:51,564
Tell me

741
00:31:51,564 --> 00:31:53,084
which address you live at.

742
00:31:53,764 --> 00:31:55,184
It's

743
00:31:55,184 --> 00:31:56,804
Np. 173 Binhai Road 3.

744
00:31:58,405 --> 00:32:00,284
Road 3 isn't in the demolition zone.

745
00:32:02,324 --> 00:32:03,084
What?

746
00:32:05,284 --> 00:32:06,904
(That's for today's Dongjiang News.)

747
00:32:07,204 --> 00:32:08,244
(Thank you for watching.)

748
00:32:08,564 --> 00:32:09,564
(See you tomorrow.)

749
00:32:18,445 --> 00:32:19,605
It's meeting time now.

750
00:32:20,084 --> 00:32:21,592
You just stay.

751
00:32:21,804 --> 00:32:22,724
Let's hold it here.

752
00:32:23,885 --> 00:32:24,244
Okay.

753
00:32:24,885 --> 00:32:26,125
I'll go call Mr. Zheng.

754
00:32:29,605 --> 00:32:31,484
Mr. Zheng, the meeting is starting.

755
00:32:32,524 --> 00:32:34,125
Ms. Li will hold it in the courtyard.

756
00:32:34,405 --> 00:32:35,004
Alright.

757
00:32:35,244 --> 00:32:36,484
Let me.

758
00:32:36,484 --> 00:32:37,084
Put it here.

759
00:32:37,084 --> 00:32:37,445
Okay.

760
00:32:39,564 --> 00:32:39,885
Okay.

761
00:32:44,244 --> 00:32:45,804
Now, everyone report

762
00:32:46,685 --> 00:32:47,804
your negotiation progress.

763
00:32:51,724 --> 00:32:52,445
I'll start first.

764
00:32:53,365 --> 00:32:56,284
I talked to 15 households. Five signed.

765
00:32:56,564 --> 00:32:57,965
Three are still hesitating.

766
00:32:58,645 --> 00:33:00,605
Seven refused to sign.

767
00:33:02,405 --> 00:33:03,165
Just sign it.

768
00:33:11,764 --> 00:33:12,165
You sign?

769
00:33:12,165 --> 00:33:13,244
You fell asleep.

770
00:33:13,244 --> 00:33:14,804
Well, meeting starts.

771
00:33:15,084 --> 00:33:17,125
Your turn. How did your negotiations go?

772
00:33:17,845 --> 00:33:18,845
How many signed?

773
00:33:19,244 --> 00:33:21,165
I negotiated with 15 households,
five signed.

774
00:33:22,405 --> 00:33:23,284
That's not many.

775
00:33:24,524 --> 00:33:26,645
I negotiated with 13 households.

776
00:33:28,125 --> 00:33:30,284
See this blister on my lip?

777
00:33:30,685 --> 00:33:33,885
And... Three signed.

778
00:33:36,764 --> 00:33:38,885
Three is good. Small gains add up.

779
00:33:48,284 --> 00:33:49,845
Mr. Zheng, Ms. Li.

780
00:33:50,605 --> 00:33:52,605
Can I stop doing this?

781
00:33:53,044 --> 00:33:55,804
I'm not suited for this.

782
00:33:56,165 --> 00:33:57,524
Is this the time to pick tasks?

783
00:33:58,284 --> 00:33:59,365
Time is tight.

784
00:33:59,845 --> 00:34:01,464
Even a general must charge into battle.

785
00:34:01,724 --> 00:34:03,405
Suited or not, you must do it.

786
00:34:03,885 --> 00:34:05,165
Well, I spoke to five today.

787
00:34:06,205 --> 00:34:07,645
Not a single one agreed.

788
00:34:07,804 --> 00:34:10,765
Mr. Zheng, he's tried his best.

789
00:34:11,124 --> 00:34:12,725
But he got worked up easily.

790
00:34:12,925 --> 00:34:14,684
- You know when he's working...
- I know.

791
00:34:15,405 --> 00:34:16,056
What about you?

792
00:34:18,725 --> 00:34:20,204
I negotiated with eight households.

793
00:34:21,524 --> 00:34:23,564
But only one signed.

794
00:34:23,805 --> 00:34:25,644
So you two only got one signed?

795
00:34:26,765 --> 00:34:27,325
That's tough.

796
00:34:27,765 --> 00:34:28,084
Yes.

797
00:34:28,760 --> 00:34:29,245
It's fine.

798
00:34:30,765 --> 00:34:32,644
Let's take it step by step, okay?

799
00:34:32,805 --> 00:34:34,644
I've only managed to secure three.

800
00:34:35,725 --> 00:34:38,004
Li, you seem to have a way with this.

801
00:34:38,484 --> 00:34:39,288
How about this?

802
00:34:39,288 --> 00:34:41,285
Tomorrow, bring Lin with you.

803
00:34:41,684 --> 00:34:43,325
Let him learn from you, okay?

804
00:34:44,644 --> 00:34:45,124
Sure.

805
00:34:46,325 --> 00:34:48,004
Where's Mr. Tan?

806
00:34:49,245 --> 00:34:50,365
Is he still working?

807
00:34:50,805 --> 00:34:53,208
Wait, I haven't seen him for days.

808
00:34:54,644 --> 00:34:56,056
- Where did he go?
- He threw down his hat.

809
00:34:57,765 --> 00:35:00,644
- What does that mean?
- It's Wu dialect for "quitting".

810
00:35:01,285 --> 00:35:04,120
Hearing that this project

811
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:06,044
needs 150 million,

812
00:35:06,365 --> 00:35:07,445
he couldn't sleep at all.

813
00:35:08,484 --> 00:35:09,752
He insisted in talking with me.

814
00:35:09,845 --> 00:35:11,960
Right. He came to me too.

815
00:35:13,564 --> 00:35:14,840
Something just occurred to me.

816
00:35:15,004 --> 00:35:17,604
A few days ago, I saw Mr. Tan

817
00:35:18,644 --> 00:35:22,164
writing a letter of resignation.

818
00:35:45,528 --> 00:35:48,056
(Letter of Resignation)

819
00:35:53,560 --> 00:35:59,608
(Super Dog Restaurant)

820
00:36:12,084 --> 00:36:12,564
Come in.

821
00:36:16,845 --> 00:36:17,365
Here you are.

822
00:36:24,845 --> 00:36:25,124
Sit.

823
00:36:29,445 --> 00:36:30,004
Hungry?

824
00:36:30,845 --> 00:36:31,325
Just eat.

825
00:36:32,285 --> 00:36:34,604
Well, these years,

826
00:36:36,365 --> 00:36:38,164
you've never eaten here.

827
00:36:39,044 --> 00:36:41,004
Every time you just paid,

828
00:36:41,484 --> 00:36:42,684
took the receipt, and left.

829
00:36:44,124 --> 00:36:44,925
Try this.

830
00:36:45,805 --> 00:36:47,084
Shrimp dumplings are tasty.

831
00:36:47,204 --> 00:36:48,044
Thank you.

832
00:36:50,484 --> 00:36:50,965
Don't worry.

833
00:36:51,765 --> 00:36:52,965
I'm paying today.

834
00:36:53,725 --> 00:36:54,925
No need for you to pay

835
00:36:55,245 --> 00:36:56,644
or issue invoices.

836
00:36:58,124 --> 00:36:58,725
Eat.

837
00:37:00,725 --> 00:37:01,164
Hurry.

838
00:37:03,684 --> 00:37:04,504
You read the letter.

839
00:37:04,725 --> 00:37:05,245
Right.

840
00:37:08,725 --> 00:37:11,004
If there's something to say,
just say it directly.

841
00:37:12,405 --> 00:37:12,805
No.

842
00:37:13,965 --> 00:37:14,405
Nothing.

843
00:37:17,285 --> 00:37:18,885
We've known each other for years.

844
00:37:19,405 --> 00:37:22,805
We never had time to have
a good chat and drink.

845
00:37:23,245 --> 00:37:26,164
Today happens to be a good chance
to see you off.

846
00:37:28,925 --> 00:37:29,285
Here.

847
00:37:30,044 --> 00:37:31,032
Thank you, Mr. Zheng.

848
00:37:38,245 --> 00:37:39,164
Also,

849
00:37:40,285 --> 00:37:41,524
I need your advice.

850
00:37:42,725 --> 00:37:45,245
Once you leave,
who's going to manage the accounts?

851
00:37:46,684 --> 00:37:48,965
Yuehai's project is so complex.

852
00:37:49,524 --> 00:37:51,965
The finances are huge.
Who can manage them?

853
00:37:52,325 --> 00:37:53,684
I need someone trustworthy.

854
00:37:55,044 --> 00:37:57,084
How about Xie? What do you think?

855
00:37:57,084 --> 00:37:59,245
Xie? He won't do.

856
00:37:59,445 --> 00:38:02,405
He's too careless.

857
00:38:03,845 --> 00:38:04,204
Right.

858
00:38:05,245 --> 00:38:06,285
Xie

859
00:38:06,725 --> 00:38:08,044
can be in charge of logistics.

860
00:38:09,044 --> 00:38:10,445
But managing finances? No.

861
00:38:10,604 --> 00:38:11,725
Numbers just confuse him.

862
00:38:14,325 --> 00:38:15,325
How about Lin?

863
00:38:15,725 --> 00:38:18,712
Many people
are in his project department.

864
00:38:18,712 --> 00:38:19,576
He has time.

865
00:38:19,684 --> 00:38:21,325
Lin is not really suitable either.

866
00:38:21,765 --> 00:38:24,684
He's just not cut out
for reading reports.

867
00:38:25,084 --> 00:38:25,644
What to do?

868
00:38:26,124 --> 00:38:27,124
I definitely can't do it.

869
00:38:27,124 --> 00:38:28,604
I'm too busy.

870
00:38:29,524 --> 00:38:31,896
Ms. Li is capable,

871
00:38:32,245 --> 00:38:33,644
but she's busy too.

872
00:38:34,285 --> 00:38:36,644
She may make a mistake when busy.

873
00:38:38,084 --> 00:38:39,814
Anyway, you need to find

874
00:38:40,088 --> 00:38:41,204
a capable professional

875
00:38:42,445 --> 00:38:43,805
to take this on.

876
00:38:44,805 --> 00:38:45,245
Exactly.

877
00:38:46,405 --> 00:38:48,684
That's why I want your advice.

878
00:38:49,164 --> 00:38:50,604
Come on, drink.

879
00:38:58,725 --> 00:39:00,564
I just remembered something.

880
00:39:02,885 --> 00:39:08,684
How did you and your wife separate?
Well, I know.

881
00:39:09,164 --> 00:39:10,084
You told me before.

882
00:39:10,725 --> 00:39:14,285
But it's been a long time.
I've forgotten.

883
00:39:15,484 --> 00:39:16,484
Maybe I'm getting old.

884
00:39:17,604 --> 00:39:18,765
My mind's not as sharp.

885
00:39:20,004 --> 00:39:21,164
Playing the emotional card?

886
00:39:21,925 --> 00:39:23,004
No.

887
00:39:24,484 --> 00:39:27,004
Alright, if you want
to rip open my old wound,

888
00:39:27,285 --> 00:39:28,285
I'll just show it to you.

889
00:39:29,084 --> 00:39:30,084
I'll tell it again.

890
00:39:31,405 --> 00:39:32,440
Back then,

891
00:39:33,325 --> 00:39:35,564
my wife and I were still young.

892
00:39:37,245 --> 00:39:39,684
We begged our way to Yuehai.

893
00:39:40,885 --> 00:39:43,044
Thinking the place was nice,

894
00:39:43,325 --> 00:39:44,365
we settled here.

895
00:39:44,644 --> 00:39:46,524
During the day, we went out begging.

896
00:39:48,564 --> 00:39:50,965
At night, once it got dark,

897
00:39:51,325 --> 00:39:52,325
we'd meet

898
00:39:52,524 --> 00:39:53,965
under that tree. You know it.

899
00:39:55,044 --> 00:39:56,124
We met under it.

900
00:39:58,484 --> 00:40:01,245
One day, she didn't come back.

901
00:40:02,524 --> 00:40:05,164
So I searched.
I had searched for so many years.

902
00:40:06,684 --> 00:40:08,164
Every time I changed jobs

903
00:40:08,204 --> 00:40:09,805
or moved,

904
00:40:09,885 --> 00:40:12,044
I'd call the local police station

905
00:40:12,084 --> 00:40:13,285
to leave my contact.

906
00:40:14,325 --> 00:40:17,365
Hoping that if she ever came back,

907
00:40:17,684 --> 00:40:18,484
she could find me.

908
00:40:24,765 --> 00:40:27,484
I kept searching and waiting.
It's been thirty years.

909
00:40:28,204 --> 00:40:29,204
Thirty years. I...

910
00:40:29,405 --> 00:40:30,725
Honestly, I stopped hoping

911
00:40:31,044 --> 00:40:32,765
a long time ago.

912
00:40:33,644 --> 00:40:34,245
But,

913
00:40:36,084 --> 00:40:38,245
what else can I do?
I've been doing it all these years.

914
00:40:38,245 --> 00:40:40,725
It's just... It's become a habit.

915
00:40:41,604 --> 00:40:42,004
Of course.

916
00:40:42,524 --> 00:40:44,044
I know

917
00:40:44,084 --> 00:40:46,164
you transferred me to Yuehai

918
00:40:46,204 --> 00:40:47,604
because you knew about this.

919
00:40:47,725 --> 00:40:49,725
You wanted to let me

920
00:40:49,725 --> 00:40:50,845
wait for my wife here.

921
00:40:51,524 --> 00:40:52,084
I really...

922
00:40:52,124 --> 00:40:54,164
I'm very grateful to you.

923
00:40:54,805 --> 00:40:56,925
But Mr. Zheng, I must make it clear.

924
00:40:57,164 --> 00:40:58,904
This thing

925
00:40:59,004 --> 00:41:01,484
has nothing to do

926
00:41:01,604 --> 00:41:02,725
with my feelings for Yuehai.

927
00:41:09,805 --> 00:41:10,776
You still remember that?

928
00:41:14,004 --> 00:41:16,564
But there's one thing you got wrong.

929
00:41:18,365 --> 00:41:19,325
If you think

930
00:41:19,604 --> 00:41:22,168
I transferred you here

931
00:41:22,168 --> 00:41:23,564
just for your wife,

932
00:41:24,124 --> 00:41:26,405
you underestimated me.
And this matter too.

933
00:41:27,684 --> 00:41:28,885
I transferred you here because

934
00:41:29,885 --> 00:41:30,564
I know you.

935
00:41:32,044 --> 00:41:33,164
I know you're capable.

936
00:41:33,885 --> 00:41:36,084
You're kind and conscientious.

937
00:41:36,644 --> 00:41:39,365
You know I have a short temper.

938
00:41:39,684 --> 00:41:40,604
I'm impulsive.

939
00:41:41,365 --> 00:41:44,285
Only you can rein me in

940
00:41:45,084 --> 00:41:45,805
and hold me back.

941
00:41:46,564 --> 00:41:47,004
Right?

942
00:41:48,044 --> 00:41:48,792
Mr. Zheng.

943
00:41:49,816 --> 00:41:51,405
If you put it that way...

944
00:41:51,725 --> 00:41:52,684
I'm telling the truth.

945
00:41:52,965 --> 00:41:55,004
But these years,
I never managed to hold you back.

946
00:41:55,965 --> 00:41:56,632
You're wrong.

947
00:41:58,965 --> 00:42:01,524
Well, Mr. Zheng,
since you've brought it up,

948
00:42:03,684 --> 00:42:06,164
I must say.

949
00:42:06,604 --> 00:42:07,416
Personally,

950
00:42:07,512 --> 00:42:11,084
I have no objection
to the land reclamation project.

951
00:42:11,725 --> 00:42:13,336
It's truly

952
00:42:14,204 --> 00:42:15,084
a very advanced

953
00:42:15,325 --> 00:42:17,400
and impressive

954
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:18,524
technology.

955
00:42:18,564 --> 00:42:20,604
And higher authorities support it.

956
00:42:21,245 --> 00:42:22,725
But the people don't understand.

957
00:42:23,684 --> 00:42:26,684
No matter how we explain it,
they won't accept it.

958
00:42:27,044 --> 00:42:28,285
The work can't move forward.

959
00:42:28,965 --> 00:42:29,564
Tan.

960
00:42:31,124 --> 00:42:33,405
Cut those official lines.

961
00:42:34,285 --> 00:42:35,325
Don't you know me?

962
00:42:36,524 --> 00:42:38,445
I want the truth. Okay?

963
00:42:39,084 --> 00:42:39,644
Just tell me,

964
00:42:40,925 --> 00:42:42,965
are you scared?

965
00:42:43,445 --> 00:42:45,484
Are you afraid to take responsibility?

966
00:42:45,925 --> 00:42:47,524
Say it. I want the truth.

967
00:42:47,765 --> 00:42:48,204
Say it.

968
00:42:58,845 --> 00:42:59,495
Yes.

969
00:43:00,536 --> 00:43:01,445
I am scared.

970
00:43:06,280 --> 00:43:10,990
♪Gently holding your face♪

971
00:43:13,340 --> 00:43:18,588
♪To dry the tears from your eyes♪

972
00:43:20,148 --> 00:43:25,341
♪My heart will always be yours♪

973
00:43:27,156 --> 00:43:32,492
♪Tell me you'll never be alone again♪

974
00:43:34,120 --> 00:43:38,108
♪Gazing deep into your eyes♪

975
00:43:41,028 --> 00:43:46,397
♪No further words are needed♪

976
00:43:48,033 --> 00:43:53,238
♪Tightly holding your hand♪

977
00:43:54,972 --> 00:44:00,332
♪The warmth has never changed♪

978
00:44:01,448 --> 00:44:04,556
♪We share the joy♪

979
00:44:04,884 --> 00:44:08,108
♪We share the pain♪

980
00:44:08,362 --> 00:44:13,933
♪We hold the same hope deep inside♪

981
00:44:15,373 --> 00:44:18,372
♪We brave the storm♪

982
00:44:18,892 --> 00:44:21,884
♪We share the quest♪

983
00:44:22,325 --> 00:44:28,268
♪We cherish this love we share♪

984
00:44:31,458 --> 00:44:36,514
♪Whether we've ever met before♪

985
00:44:38,419 --> 00:44:43,829
♪Be it near or far away♪

986
00:44:45,420 --> 00:44:50,603
♪My heartfelt wish for you♪

987
00:44:52,387 --> 00:44:57,517
♪Is for your peace and happiness♪

988
00:44:58,824 --> 00:45:01,994
♪We share the joy♪

989
00:45:02,252 --> 00:45:05,320
♪We share the pain♪

990
00:45:05,744 --> 00:45:11,967
♪We hold the same hope deep inside♪

991
00:45:12,567 --> 00:45:15,630
♪We brave the storm♪

992
00:45:15,966 --> 00:45:19,054
♪We share the quest♪

993
00:45:19,350 --> 00:45:25,527
♪We cherish this love we share♪
